@node not08 "OLOFIGHT IS NOW AVAILABLE"

@{B}OLOFIGHT@{UB} IS NOW AVAILABLE
-------------------------

@{I}PRESS RELEASE @{UI}

@{B}OloFight@{UB} is finished! Official release of this outstanding title was at @{B}Computer
'98@{UB}  show  (Cologne)  and  then available from all good @{B}Amiga@{UB} dealers around the
world!

@{B}OloFight@{UB}  is  a  beat'em  up game which introduces many innovations over similar
existing  @{B}Amiga@{UB} titles. It's produced in Italy by a new software house, @{B}The Real
Ologram@{UB}.

@{I}FEATURES @{UI}:
   * 10 different fighters with more than 400 animation frames each
   * 25fps animations
   * 10 special moves for each of the fighters
   * power-ups to strenghten fighters and 'buy' 4 special moves of varying power
     (out of the ten available for each player), whose control is easier than in
     other similar titles
   * realistic  collision  detection:  the more precise your moves are, the more
     harm they will cause!
   * more  than 3000 (three thousand!) colours on screen at the same time on any
     @{B}AGA Amiga@{UB}
   * objects moving on different parallax layers, behind/in front of fighters
   * floor with 3D perspective motion!
   * background music adapting itself to the game events
   * 100% rendered graphics
   * animated backgrounds
   * shadow effect reflecting fighters' movements
   * multilingual support
   * many playing modes (story, survival, time attack, one-on-one, etc.)

It  will  also  handle high-scores for each of the modes through our web server,
thus allowing you to rival with other players all over the world!

In @{B}OloFight@{UB}'s world, every match increases the players' experience, according to
the  difficulty  of  the match itself. As a character gets more experience, both
his skills and his special moves get stronger. On top of that, new special moves
are  discovered.  A  more powerful fighter means a higher score and consequently
higher  position  in  the  various  ranks,  including the general ones which are
managed by our web server, thus making you compete with other users worldwide.
@{I}REQUIREMENTS @{UI}:
The  game  is available on floppy disks and CD, runs on any @{B}AGA@{UB}-based @{B}Amiga@{UB} with
at  least  0.7Mb  ChipRAM and 1.8Mb FastRAM. If you own the floppy version or if
you want to install it from the CD, 10Mbytes of HD space are required.

A patch for Gfx board will come soon!

@{I}RECOMMENDED @{UI}:
   * @{B}MC68030@{UB}+,
   * extra RAM,
   * CD-Drive 4X (if played from the CD drive).

@{I}WHERE TO GET IT @{UI}:
The game can be bought from us and from all @{B}Amiga@{UB} dealers.

The  most  convenient  method of placing an order is to use our electronic order
form  located  at @{B}http://www.ologram.com/order.html@{UB}. You can also send an E-Mail
to  @{I}sales@ologram.com @{UI} or  a  FAX  including  your  address (the phone number is
required!), the payment method and what version you want to buy (floppy or CD).

A  demo  is  available  on  our  web  site at @{B}www.ologram.com@{UB} and on @{B}Aminet@{UB} (dir
game/demo).

