@node not09 "AMAZING AND INFORMER COMBINE"

@{B}AMAZING@{UB} AND @{B}INFORMER@{UB} COMBINE
----------------------------

Joint  Press  Release from @{B}Eldritch Enterprises@{UB} and @{B}PiM Publications@{UB}, January 5,
1999.

@{B}PiM   Publications@{UB},   publishers   of   @{B}Amazing  Computing/Amiga@{UB},  and  @{B}Eldritch
Enterprises@{UB},  publishers  of @{B}The Amiga Informer@{UB}, are proud to announce that they
have  combined  their  efforts into one publication. This magazine will maintain
the  @{B}Amazing  Computing/Amiga@{UB}  title  and continue to be distributed through @{B}PiM
Publications@{UB}.  @{I}Fletcher  Haug, @{UI} the  Editor-in-chief of @{B}The Amiga Informer@{UB}, will
join  the  staff  of  @{B}Amazing@{UB}  and bring with him many of the resources from @{UB}The
Informer@{UB}.  @{I}"It  is  vital that the @{B}Amiga@{UB} community retain a print publication in
North  America," @{UI} said  @{I}Haug. @{UI} @{I}"By  combining  the  efforts  of @{B}The Informer@{UB} and
@{B}Amazing@{UB}, I feel we will be able to give our readers and the community a stronger
publication  that  combines  the  best qualities of both magazines. I am looking
forward to working with @{B}PiM Publications@{UB} on this project." @{UI}

Since  North  America  was  served  by  @{B}Amazing  Computing/Amiga@{UB}  and  @{B}The Amiga
Informer@{UB},  both  magazines  were in competition for the same advertising dollars
and  subscribers. In recent months, it has become clear the North American @{B}Amiga@{UB}
would  benefit  from  a  single  newsstand  distributed  publication. @{I}"These are
critical  times  for  the  @{B}Amiga@{UB}  marketplace  as  @{B}Amiga  Inc.@{UB} prepares the Next
Generation  @{B}Amiga@{UB}  and @{B}OS 3.5@{UB} remains in development," @{UI}stated @{B}Amazing@{UB}'s Managing
Editor, @{I}Don Hicks. @{UI}@{I}"We believe the best way to serve this industry is to combine
our   efforts   and   build  a  stronger  communication  network  from  the  two
publications.  With  this  alliance,  we can offer @{B}Amiga@{UB} vendors an unparalleled
opportunity  to  the @{B}Amiga@{UB} marketplace in North America while giving our readers
the best possible service." @{UI}

@{B}The  Amiga  Informer@{UB}  magazine  was  launched  in  April,  1996 and grew to be a
respected  publication  providing  Amigans  with insightful information and news
compiled  by  freelance  authors  worldwide.  Issue 17 of @{B}The Amiga Informer@{UB} was
recently  released  and  it  will  be  the  last  issue printed. As  part of the
arrangement  between @{B}Amazing@{UB} and @{B}The Informer@{UB}, @{B}PiM Publications@{UB} will fulfill any
outstanding   subscriptions   from   @{B}The   Informer@{UB}   with   issues  of  @{B}Amazing
Computing/Amiga@{UB}.  @{B}Eldritch  Enterprises@{UB} closed as a business, effective December
31,  1998.  Further information will soon become available at @{B}The Amiga Informer@{UB}
website    (@{B}www.amigainformer.com@{UB})    and    the   @{B}Amazing   Computing@{UB}   website
(@{B}www.pimpub.com@{UB}).

@{B}Amazing Computing/Amiga@{UB} was the world's first monthly @{B}Amiga@{UB} magazine and remains
the  longest  running  @{B}Amiga@{UB} publication. For over 13 years, @{B}AC@{UB} has provided the
@{B}Amiga@{UB}  community with balanced, thoughtful reporting on the @{B}Amiga@{UB} market. The @{B}AC@{UB}
staff has also been instrumental in providing video tapes and transcripts of the
major  events  in  the  @{B}Amiga@{UB}  community. With the combined efforts of @{B}Amazing@{UB}'s
Amazing  Authors and @{B}The Amiga Informer@{UB}'s quality staff, the @{B}Amiga@{UB} community has
an opportunity to build an even better future publication.

We  hope  that  the  combining of @{B}Amazing Computing/Amiga@{UB} and @{B}The Amiga Informer@{UB}
will  prove  to make a stronger publication that can continue to serve the @{B}Amiga@{UB}
community  and  carry it to the next level of @{B}Amiga@{UB} computing. With the combined
efforts  of both magazines' staff focused in the same direction, we believe that
the  community will be better served and will continue to get the information it
needs to move forward to the future.

Sincerely,

@{I}Fletcher Haug, @{UI}@{B}The Amiga Informer Magazine@{UB}

@{I}Don Hicks, @{UI}@{B}Amazing Computing/Amiga@{UB}
