@node not10 "SHAPESHIFTER GOES FREEWARE!!!"

@{B}SHAPESHIFTER@{UB} GOES FREEWARE!!!
-----------------------------

@{B}ShapeShifter@{UB}  is a multitasking freeware @{B}Macintosh-II@{UB} emulator for the @{B}Amiga@{UB} and
@{B}DraCo@{UB}  computers.  It  allows  to  run  @{B}Macintosh@{UB} software concurrently to @{B}Amiga@{UB}
applications without hardware add-ons or modifications.

Some of the emulation's features:
   * Supports @{B}MacOS 7.1@{UB} thru @{B}8.1@{UB}.
   * Color  display  up to 256 colors on @{B}AGA Amiga@{UB}s (16 colors on @{B}ECS@{UB}) and up to
     16.7 million colors on graphics cards.
   * Accelerated graphics with @{B}CyberGraphX@{UB}/@{B}Picasso96@{UB}.
   * Support for one or two monitors.
   * No MMU required, even runs on @{B}A1200@{UB}.
   * @{B}Macintosh@{UB}  hard  disks  can  be simulated in @{B}Amiga@{UB} files or @{B}Amiga@{UB} hard disk
     partitions.
   * Can  use  @{B}Amiga@{UB} floppy drives, serial, parallel and SCSI ports from the @{B}Mac@{UB}
     @{B}Mac@{UB}  HD  disks can be read directly with an HD floppy drive, @{B}Mac@{UB} 720K disks
     can be used with any @{B}Amiga@{UB} floppy drive. To use @{B}Mac@{UB} 800K disks, you have to
     own  @{B}CrossMAC@{UB}  and  an  original  @{B}Mac@{UB} drive. @{B}ShapeShifter@{UB} also supports the
     @{B}Catweasel@{UB} controller.
   * 8 bit stereo sound output (sound cards supported via @{B}AHI@{UB}).
   * Sound input with parallel-port sound digitizers.
   * Access to Ethernet networks.
   * Simple networking between two @{B}Amiga@{UB}s with PLIP.
   * Text clipboard sharing between @{B}Mac@{UB} and @{B}Amiga@{UB}.
   * File handler to access @{B}Macintosh@{UB} volumes from the @{B}Workbench@{UB}.
   * Speed comparable to a real @{B}Mac@{UB} with equivalent hardware.

@{I}Requirements @{UI}:
   * @{B}OS2.1@{UB}
   * @{B}68020@{UB} processor
   * 4MB of RAM
   * HD floppy drive recommended.

A  copy of a @{B}Macintosh@{UB} 512K or 1MB ROM and the @{B}Macintosh@{UB} system software are not
included,  but  required.  The  ROM  can  be  read  off of a real @{B}Mac@{UB} by using a
supplied  program,  the system software can be bought from @{B}Apple@{UB}. Note, however,
that  reading  the  ROM  is only legal if you have bought the ROMs or own a real
@{B}Macintosh@{UB}.

The most important changes in V3.10:
   * @{B}ShapeShifter@{UB}  is  now  freeware  (keyfile  no  longer  needed to enable all
     features).
   * @{B}MacOS 8@{UB} support (requires 1MB ROM).
   * @{B}Picasso96@{UB}  PIP  (15  bit  color  depth) is used in "@{B}Amiga@{UB} Window" mode when
     available.
