@node not31 "1998: WHAT'S ANOTHER YEAR"

1998: WHAT'S ANOTHER YEAR
-------------------------

February 1998
  * @{B}Nordic  Global  Inc.@{UB}  released  the  new  version  3.0 of the popular TCP/IP
    protocol stack @{B}Miami@{UB}.
  * The  source  for  @{B}AMOS@{UB}  + @{B}AMOSPro@{UB} (including the compiler) was released to a
    small  team  of  developers, who wish to put this once ever-popular language
    back on top of them all, by giving it a major overhaul.
  * @{B}ICOA@{UB} was finally open to accept membership applications from developers.
  * @{B}Index  Information  Ltd@{UB},  @{B}Blittersoft@{UB} and @{B}Phase 5 Digital Products@{UB} announced
    cooperation on @{B}PowerPC@{UB} Technology for the @{B}Amiga@{UB}.
  * @{B}Haage & Partner@{UB} announced new versions of @{B}X-DVE@{UB} and @{B}FontMachine@{UB}.
  * @{I}Petro  Tyschtschenko@{UI}  confirmed in an interview that the chosen approach for
    new @{B}Amiga@{UB} models would be @{B}68k@{UB}+@{B}PPC@{UB}.
  * @{I}Paul  Carrington@{UI},  from  @{B}Vulcan@{UB}  explained  the reasons for exploring @{B}PC@{UB} and
    @{B}PlayStation@{UB} development.
  * The  number  of  @{B}PPC@{UB} developments for Amiga was increasing. Then, it was the
    turn of Datatypes.

March 1998
  * @{B}Wordworth  7.0@{UB},  undoubtably  the World's best-selling @{B}Amiga@{UB} word processor,
    was released.
  * @{B}Saku  98@{UB} was the biggest @{B}Amiga@{UB} only event in Finland in years. The new @{B}Amiga@{UB}
    hymn of @{I}Petro Tyschtschenko@{UI} was launched there.
  * @{B}Alive  MediaSoft@{UB}  entered  in  another  area  of the @{B}Amiga@{UB} - "Kids Software"
    which  is  a  very  important  market for kids nowadays which allows them to
    learn how to use computers.
  * @{B}COMPUQUICK  Media  Center@{UB} and @{B}National AMIGA@{UB} were exclusive distributors for
    the sale of @{B}AMIGA 1200@{UB} and @{B}A1200-HDD@{UB} for userclub members.
  * @{B}Siamese  Systems  Ltd@{UB}  decided to launch the new @{B}"Siamese Remote Amiga v2.1"@{UB}
    package  to use as a full Serial based system in its own right, or evaluated
    and  then  part exchanged for the full @{B}"Siamese V2.5 Pro"@{UB} package, by paying
    the diference.
  * The  best  MIDI  sequencer  @{B}Bars  &  Pipes Prof. 2.5b@{UB} for the @{B}Amiga@{UB} was then
    downloadable.
  * @{B}HiSOFT@{UB}  announced  that  version  1.2 of @{B}iBrowse@{UB}, the world wide web browser
    that is used by more @{B}Amiga@{UB} users than any other browser, was then available.
  * @{B}Nova  Design,  Inc.@{UB}  announced  that  the  exciting  version  3.0 upgrade to
    @{B}ImageFX@{UB} was then shipping.
  * @{B}VoyagerNG  2.95@{UB},  the  first public release of @{B}VoyagerNG@{UB} since version 2.88,
    was then avalaible.
  * @{B}AMIGA  International,  Inc.@{UB} and @{B}Phase 5 Digital Products@{UB} announced that they
    had signed a license agreement for the @{B}AMIGA OS 3.1@{UB} which will allow @{B}Phase 5@{UB}
    to use @{B}AMIGA OS 3.1@{UB} in future products.
  * @{B}Asimware  Innovations  Inc.@{UB}  released  new  versions  of  @{B}AsimCDFS  v3.9@{UB} and
    @{B}MasterISO@{UB}.

April 1998:
  * @{B}Asimware  Innovations  Inc.@{UB}  added @{B}MasterISO v2@{UB} Development documents at his
    WEB site and they also started two mailing lists; for @{B}AsimCDFS Version 3@{UB} and
    @{B}MasterISO Version 2@{UB}.
  * @{I}Ossowski@{UI}'s   @{B}Schatztruhe@{UB}  announces  availability  of  @{B}Aminet  CD  24@{UB}  which
    featured a special @{B}Aminet@{UB}-version of @{B}IBrowse 1.2@{UB}, the famous browser.

May 1998:
